<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ideffffb0a-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7233"><num value="7233">§ 7233.</num><heading> Term of loans</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="ideffffb0b-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7233/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Term of loan</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In the case of each loan commodity (other than upland cotton or extra long staple cotton), a marketing assistance loan under <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s7231">section 7231 of this title</ref> shall have a term of 9 months beginning on the first day of the first month after the month in which the loan is made.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="ideffffb0c-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7233/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Special rule for cotton</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A marketing assistance loan for upland cotton or extra long staple cotton shall have a term of 10 months beginning on the first day of the month in which the loan is made.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="ideffffb0d-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7233/c"><num value="c" class="bold">(c)</num><heading class="bold"> Extensions prohibited</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may not extend the term of a marketing assistance loan for any loan commodity.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="ideffffb0e-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/104/127/tI/s133">Pub. L. 104–127, title I, § 133</ref>, <date date="1996-04-04">Apr. 4, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/907">110 Stat. 907</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
